an><hr size=1> Great guide <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...one quick comment to add.  The &quot;random&quot; timing of the aggro you mentioned in several of your techniques is not really random...it represents the server round-robining its way through the zone's mobs updating their hate lists one by one as fast as it can.  If you get lucky, you might catch a group of mobs at the right time and not aggro them when you otherwise would (this is why you can sometimes just run straight through a couple of mobs that are looking right you without getting aggroed).<br><br>I know what you're thinking:<br>Since this is server timing and the monk has no way of knowing which mobs are updating when, we might as well call it random, right?<br><br>Almost, but not quite.  The number of people in zone, the number of mobs in zone, the server's lag in general to some degree all affect the round robin delay...so, in general, it's easier to attempt to use the round robin factor in your pulls when the load on the server/zone is high.  Notice I said &quot;easier&quot; and not necessarily &quot;safer&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...if the server/zone load is high, you incur your own additional risks associated with that high load. <p>Gondil Stonefriend</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uauntiehiss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Auntiehiss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/23/01 2:48:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Laotzu's Guide, eye of zomm, firework #4...</span><hr size=1> I know some monks have said to me, when I asked, that they make use of eye of zomm on some pulls. I don't feel qualified to comment on that, as at level 40 I have yet to be in a situation where I thought that was worth a try. Still, I have used it with my wizzie and magician in some rare cases (FD would vastly increase the utility I'm sure).<br><br>Obviously there are many items that can proc EoZ including the obvious tinkered one.<br><br>When tinkering went in it was possible for a brand new gnome to make fireworks with a fairly high success rate. I do not know if this is still true. For many many months thereafter it was true that firework number 4 (you get four each time you tinker them) would actually cause a targeted mob to aggro. This firework is like a bolt spell, has a fairly long range and slow travel with delayed hit of target effect. <br><br>Like EoZ this allows(ed at least) increasing the distance from the mob/s after unleashing the aggro [e.g. you used to be able to autorun away from casting point on EoZ as wizzie/mage in the second or so it took for change to EoZ view/control].<br><br>Lastly, for monks like myself, who don't yet have access to high level shuriken, if you are or support up to a mid 20s player killing batlings in Warrens (trivia rule kills non-xp loot if magic, nodrop, or lore) they commonly drop very light shuriken (one, maybe two, tenths) with 120 range.<br><br>Auntiehiss, 40th iksar monk on test. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ulaotzuqigong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LaotzuQigong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/24/01 3:13:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Laotzu's Guide to Advanced Pulling</span><hr size=1> Good stuff...<br><br>I use eye of zomm, but only rarely.  It has very limited usage as you are typically using a charged item, so when you're doing 50 or 60 consecutive pulls it's not really practical, however there are some situations you might wanna do this in, like when you want to pull something out of a pit or canyon... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As far as additional range for pulling, if you need more range than standard shurikens, you can forge Velium shurikens (65 I think?), get a mage to summon a pouch of Quellious (100 range), buy a pumice crystal (also about 100 I think), camp a Golem metal wand (100 or so) or you can do what I like to do... forge a stack of Javelyns... 2 pounds, but stackable and 200 range.  Good as most bows 8D<br><br>LaotzuQigong<br>58 Master<br>Legendary<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usumyun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sumyun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/24/01 3:16:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/06/1371806.gif?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Laotzu's Guide to Advanced Pulling</span><hr size=1> trying to save myself some legwork here. what are a few items with root / snare charges you use and recommend? just item names are fine i can research drop locations etc.. <br>thanks,<br>Sumyun Gai<br>Silvan Rangers 